var user:new User();
user.load();

@killerspaz : here's how I use those terms.  DAO = Data Access Object, typically responsible for loading data from a db, and generally not in the AS / Flex layer.
DTO / VO = Data transfer object, and used for passing data structures between serailzation forms (eg XML, JSON).  Often deseiralzied into a ...
Model : An object which represents part of your domain.  Can perform actions on it.

public interface ILibraryServiceFacade
	{
		function select():void;
		function sync():void;
		function mediaInsertNew(items:Vector.<ICellData>):void;
		function mediaInsertKnown(items:Vector.<ICellData>):void;
		function mediaDelete(items:Vector.<ICellData>):void;
		function mediaUpdate(media:MediaItem):void;
	}
